Job_title: Data Centre Cabling & Hardware Support Engineer
Description:
ONNEC builds, supports and optimises the IT infrastructure, networks and connectivity which drive global business performance.
We are a rapidly growing organisation and finding and retaining the highest calibre of people is fundamental to us for the success of our business, we work hard to create a challenging, supportive and satisfying working environment for all our employees. ONNEC has successfully achieved the Investors in Diversity Foundational Award for our commitment to equality, diversity and inclusion in the workplace.
We re recruiting for Engineers to work within a team carrying out cabling infrastructure and network hardware support at Onnec client sites. The work will include all types of patching, break-fix, circuit provision and recovery, disconnect/reconnect of desktop and networking equipment, rack and stack of Data Centre Hardware (eg Server, Network and Storage) and provision of connectivity to DC Hardware. The position will be site based as required and reports to the Service Delivery Manager.

Description:
Help us make a big green dent in the universe. We're on a mission to drive the global renewable energy revolution, and we need loads more people to help us make our vision a reality.

About Octopus Energy

Since 2015, Octopus has been on a mission to bring affordable, green energy to the world. With the help of our in-house developed technology platform, Kraken, we’ve become the 4th largest energy supplier in the UK, opened retailers in 5 other countries, and licensed our software to retail giants including E.ON in the UK and Origin Energy in Australia. We’ve reinvented energy products with smart, data-driven tariffs to balance customer demand with renewable generation - and we’re the biggest investor in renewable generation in the UK.

We've since expanded our tentacles to Australia, and we are now looking for Data Engineer, based in Melbourne, Wellington or remote in either New Zealand or Australia. Working with Octopus Energy is a chance to join an exciting scale-up business within the energy supply sector, one that’s at the forefront of changing the landscape of the energy industry across the world. A role with us offers you the chance to contribute to building world-class operations that will catapult you into a fantastic career.

Description:
Job Title: Lead Data Engineer
Location: Sydney, NSW
Job Type: Fulltime
Job Description:
10+ years of experience - Software engineering, Cloud computing, Databricks and Big Data
Data Engineering, Data Warehousing, Solution Design, Data Analysis, Visualization and Data Modeling

Req ID: 30433
Department: THQ - ANZx ABT Program AU (30110519)
Division: Group Technology (T77000)
About the role
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head
Use Google’s cloud services to deliver real-time insights about customer behaviour
Be part of something different - working in an agile way to innovate and deliver quality outcomes at pace

At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We’re making this happen by improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our customers so they can achieve incredible things– whether they’re buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small. Join us as we reimagine our customer propositions and services using the latest platforms and technology, to better support our customers’ financial wellbeing

The Data Engineering position is critical to making this happen and your key accountabilities will include:

Building real-time analytical capability to power
Experiences within the mobile app
Informing marketing and servicing messaging
Enriching our data lake
Build data quality automated frameworks across a multi-cloud data and on premises environments
Building highly optimised data models with multiple interface types for data consumers
What will your day look like
Working in an agile framework with a team of Data Engineers to deliver data solutions for our transformation including:
Building optimized data solutions and ingestion patterns with considerations for security and data governance
Building data pipelines and a real-time data eco-system to provide interactive customer experiences that will feed data into other systems via multiple interface types.
Define and publish the data architecture standards for all applications and infrastructure across the portfolio
Foster collaboration across teams, functions, regions and divisions using a range of influencing and negotiation strategies to establish mutually beneficial partnerships with key stakeholders
What will you bring?

To grow and be successful in this role, you will ideally bring the following:

Cloud based data engineering experience
Proven successful building large data solutions
Ability to work collaboratively with technical and business teams
Ability to multi-task, highly adaptable to change and ambiguity
Proactive, shows initiative and keen to try new things i.e. new technologies

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 30433

Description:
Field Engineer – APAC
Morpheus Data is a fast-growing but established start-up focused on the unified management of hybrid clouds, containers, and infrastructure automation. Our enterprise and MSP customers can quickly enable on-premises private clouds, centralize public cloud access, and orchestrate change with cost analytics, governance policy, and automation. Out of the box, we integrate with dozens of technologies including VMware, Nutanix, AWS, Azure, GCP, Terraform, Ansible, Kubernetes, ServiceNow, and more plus co-sell and market with some of the largest OEMs and GSIs in the world including HPE, Dell, and Lenovo which gives us lots of vines to grab for digital marketing.
About The Role
Possess a practical understanding of cloud computing architecture and DevOps processes with experience deploying, self-service provisioning and automation solutions. Detail oriented and follow in depth technical documentation to properly install software and integrate solutions as various customer use cases require. We are looking for field engineer with the runway to support partners and help when POCs go a little too deep for a typical sales engineer to handle.

Let's talk about the team:

Capgemini Financial Services is a Global Strategic Business Unit that provides information technology and consultancy services to the Banking, Capital Markets and Insurance industries. Our customers count on us for the very latest in innovative service offerings & next generation global delivery.


Let’s talk about your capability and experience:

About Capgemini

At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to becoming a carbon neutral business by 2025 and net zero by 2030.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.

For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 10 years in a row.

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion

We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges. Description:
Req ID: 31691
Department: Australia Data (30290958)
Division: Australia Retail (T20000)
About the role

Data Engineer - Data Portfolio
Location: Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane
Full Time and Part Time opportunities available

At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We’re making this happen by improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our customers so they can achieve incredible things– whether they’re buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small.

The Data Engineer will be responsible for designing and creating data processing solutions that enable value from analytic models to drive rapid decision making.

A key element of this is driving the data engineering agenda within the Data Portfolio, ensuring delivery of best practice end-to-end data engineering respecting ANZ architecture standards. You will challenge inefficient engineering practise in ANZ and influence change in your field to drive better business outcomes. To this end, in the role you will implement smart and relevant data engineering to drive E2E application delivery and support the uplift of data engineering capability in Data portfolio, while linking in to the wider Enterprise Analytics roadmap.

What will your day look like
Design data structures for data ingestion, integration, and analytic layers on a variety of technologies
Working in a cross skilled squad with people both from business and technology to build end to end features
Contribute to design patterns for on-premise and cloud
Optimise data flows by building robust, fault tolerant data pipeline that cleans, transforms and aggregates unorganised and messy data into databases and data sources
What will you bring?

To grow and be successful in the role, you will ideally bring the following:

Strong Software Engineering experience with proficiency in at least one high-level programming language (Python, Java, Scala)
Experience and proficiency in at least one high-volume data processing environment (Teradata, Oracle, Cloudera, BigQuery or equivalent)
Extensive experience working within cross-functional, agile or continuous delivery teams
Strong ability to translate data insights into practical business recommendation
Strong team player
MS or BS in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics or equivalent practical experience in Data Engineering

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 31691

This role could be in Sydney, Melbourne, Canberra, Brisbane, or Adelaide.



Let’s talk about the role and responsibilities:
Collaborate with business analysts and end-users to identify requirements and develop technical specifications for software applications

Let's talk about the team:

Capgemini Financial Services is a Global Strategic Business Unit that provides information technology and consultancy services to the Banking, Capital Markets and Insurance industries. Capgemini FS brings you leading insights & deep industry experience to drive the future of Financial Services. Our customers count on us for the very latest in innovative service offerings & next generation global delivery.


Let’s talk about your capability and experience:

About Capgemini

At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to becoming a carbon neutral business by 2025 and net zero by 2030.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.

For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 10 years in a row.

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion

Don’t meet every single requirement for this role? Studies have shown women and people from diverse minority backgrounds are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single requirement. At Capgemini, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply and tell us what you can bring to the role.
We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges. If you are living with a disability, are gender diverse or neurodivergent and we can provide support with access requirements or by making an adjustment to our hiring process, please contact us at talentacquisitionaunz@capgemini.com
aunz@capgemini.com

Description:
Req ID: 31691
Department: Australia Data (30290958)
Division: Australia Retail (T20000)
About the role

Data Engineer - Data Portfolio
Location: Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane
Full Time and Part Time opportunities available

At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We’re making this happen by improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our customers so they can achieve incredible things– whether they’re buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small.

The Data Engineer will be responsible for designing and creating data processing solutions that enable value from analytic models to drive rapid decision making.

A key element of this is driving the data engineering agenda within the Data Portfolio, ensuring delivery of best practice end-to-end data engineering respecting ANZ architecture standards. You will challenge inefficient engineering practise in ANZ and influence change in your field to drive better business outcomes. To this end, in the role you will implement smart and relevant data engineering to drive E2E application delivery and support the uplift of data engineering capability in Data portfolio, while linking in to the wider Enterprise Analytics roadmap.

What will your day look like
Design data structures for data ingestion, integration, and analytic layers on a variety of technologies
Working in a cross skilled squad with people both from business and technology to build end to end features
Contribute to design patterns for on-premise and cloud
Optimise data flows by building robust, fault tolerant data pipeline that cleans, transforms and aggregates unorganised and messy data into databases and data sources
What will you bring?

To grow and be successful in the role, you will ideally bring the following:

Strong Software Engineering experience with proficiency in at least one high-level programming language (Python, Java, Scala)
Experience and proficiency in at least one high-volume data processing environment (Teradata, Oracle, Cloudera, BigQuery or equivalent)
Extensive experience working within cross-functional, agile or continuous delivery teams
Strong ability to translate data insights into practical business recommendation
Strong team player
MS or BS in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics or equivalent practical experience in Data Engineering

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 31691

Description:
Responsibilities
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.

Why Join Us
At TikTok, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for more than 1 billion users on our platform. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok.

About the TikTok Engineering Team
We are building up an engineering team for core TikTok product in Australia, to ensure TikTok continues a healthy growth, deliver the best product experience to all of our users, build the most attractive features to help users on enjoying their time on TikTok, earn trust on privacy protection, and more.

We are looking for talented individuals to join us in 2023. As a graduate, you will get unparalleled opportunities for you to kickstart your career, pursue bold ideas and explore limitless growth opportunities. Co-create a future driven by your inspiration with TikTok.

Candidates can apply to a maximum of two positions and will be considered for jobs in the order you apply. The application limit is applicable to TikTok and its affiliates' jobs globally. Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis - we encourage you to apply early.

Responsibilities
Qualifications

Description:
About the Role
We’re looking for a creative research engineer to work on building out our system’s artificial intelligence capabilities. You’re passionate about all things data, and have a keen interest in solving problems using computer vision techniques. Artificial intelligence is only useful so long as it is accurate, unbiased, and robust to any environment - you will help us achieve this within the Black.ai team.The Black.ai system utilises video data to perform its functionalities associated with identifying and understanding the way physical environments are utilised. In this role you will interact with many different aspects of the machine learning research pipeline, collaborating with our product and core engineering teams to develop our existing and new capabilities. Within the research team, you will investigate existing and novel computer vision and machine learning techniques, as well as implementing new algorithms and neural networks to solve customer problems.In this role you will work on and solve complex problems in real world environments, helping our customers improve their operational processes through impactful and intentional applications of privacy-focused artificial intelligence.
Researching existing and novel state of the art machine learning algorithms
Development and implementation of new computer vision algorithms
Implementation of unique code to improve the accuracy and efficiency of our existing neural networks
Design new approaches to processing of video data
Short-term and long-term planning of the machine learning feature set informed by findings from the product and customer success teams.
Work in an AGILE environment and develop documentation to a high standard for consumption by internal stakeholders
2+ years experience building production machine learning systems OR experience with building distributed systems, and a willingness to expand your knowledge base within machine learning and computer vision technologies
Experience using Python
Masters or PhD in fields related to computer science, mathematics, or data science OR equivalent work/industry experience
Robust understanding of mathematics and statistics
Robust coding ability
Fluent in English
Working rights within Australia
Bonus (but by no means essential):
Experience with C++ programming
Knowledge of deep learning (CNNs, Transformers, autoencoders)
Traditional machine learning (RDF, SVMs, HOG Gradient boosting)
Evidence of independently developed resources e.g. network architectures
Experience with Pytorch or TensorRT
Experience with ML Ops or Kubernetes solutions

Working at Atlassian

Atlassian can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity. Data Abstraction Platform is comprised of people with backgrounds in Java, Kotlin, Spring Boot and AWS Technologies. We are building the Transactional Data Platform (TDP) for Atlassian's Team Data. Our mission is to empower Atlassian's product teams to deliver new features, faster through managed data stores, without having to worry about enterprise requirements.

Description:
About us

Evolution Mining is a leading, growth-focused globally relevant gold company. We have grown into a globally relevant gold producer since inception in November 2011, and operate five wholly owned mines across Australia and Ontario, Canada.

At Evolution, we’re passionate about our culture and values. We are an equal opportunity employer with a commitment to diversity, offering exceptional career environments at our sites and our Group office, that are challenging, rewarding and fun for all employees. We are regularly supporting our employees’ work-life integration and provide a stimulating and inclusive environment to foster development.

About the role

The Graduate Program unlocks your potential, allowing you to develop experience and gain exposure within the Mining Engineering function, and on site. At Evolution we want to be the highlight of your careers. Some of the key result areas in this role may include:

Fulfill the requirements of the Graduate Program, including attendance at all formal workshops and webinars, and completion of assignments and deliverables to the designated timeframe

Prepare daily, weekly and monthly production plans and schedules.

Provide timely and accurate preparation of drill and blast plans.

Complete drill, blast and production daily data entry and maintain the database to a high quality.

Provide support to the Mining Manager to ensure that mining production schedules are set and maintained in line with the annual budget.

Assist where required, with the development and implementation of long-term strategic planning.

Monitor production overbreak and underbreak and identify any potential areas for improvement.

Conduct QA/QC on production activities including drill hole deviation and charge quality.

Work closely with the Geology department to ensure all scheduled grade control drilling is prioritised in weekly plans.

Work closely with the Mining Department to identify any potential cost saving initiatives.

Commit to maintaining health, safety and security standards and principles, both within own workplace and through the identification of potential risks throughout Evolution.

N.B. Should you successfully fulfill all requirements of the two-year Graduate Program, you will be offered a permanent role in the business.

About you


Qualifications in Mining Engineering.

A high degree of safety awareness with proven hazard identification and risk assessment skills.

Ability to prioritise and schedule work

Confident oral communication and presentation skills

Excellent written communication skills

Competent user of MS Office tools

April 3rd 2023

We thank you for taking the time of submitting your application. For more information, you can contact talent@evolutionmining.com

We want your perspective and ideas to help us find better ways to build our team, so we encourage you to apply no matter your age, sex or cultural background. You can be part of a committed, highly skilled team who’ll appreciate what you bring to the table. You’ll set and achieve goals and make decisions that matter, as together we help shape and contribute to the Evolution vision, including our 2050 Net Zero goal.

As part of the application process, Evolution will be collecting your personal information to assess your suitability for the role.

Description:
Req ID: 30434
Department: THQ - ANZx ABT Program AU (30110519)
Division: Group Technology (T77000)
About the role

Data Engineering Manager – ANZ Plus
Location; Melbourne/Sydney
Permanent – Full Time/Part Time

At ANZx, our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We are making this happen by improving our customers’ financial wellbeing so they can achieve incredible things – be it buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small. We are looking for people who are passionate about transformational change and to help us redefine banking for the future.

Be a part of building the ideal data ecosystem from scratch. Ensuring the right data is generated from all applications, sourced at the right velocity with the complete depth and breadth to ensure complete coverage and reuse. This is your opportunity to build new, not fix old.

This is a people leadership role (up to 5 in a team) with broad responsibilities across many aspects of our data enablement value stream.

What will your day look like
Define, create and publish the data architecture standards for all applications and infrastructure across the portfolio.
Operational data solutions that will power our new mobile apps (iOS and Android)
Analytical systems that will be used to build brand new machine learning models
MarTech systems to provide personalised real-time in-context service and marketing messages to customers that are relevant, useful and sensitive
Enable and lead a team of data engineers to be the most creative and best they can be
Influence our cloud provider’s product roadmaps to ensure they meet our needs
What will you bring?

We’re trying to reimagine the way we help and interact with our customers, so we’re looking for creativity, open mind and energy

Cloud based data engineering experience, we use GCP but we’re open to your cloud experience
Proven successful implementation of large and complex data solutions using various architectural patterns such as microservices
Ability to influence both technical and business peers and stakeholders
Leadership of engineering teams, not just their technical skills, but their careers and ambitions, you’re passionate and empathetic
Lead by example – jump on the tools when required to support the team

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 30434

Let’s talk about the role and responsibilities:
Analyses business requirements, business processes, and technical architectures. Designs and uses them as the basis for the Software Engineering solution
Let's talk about the team:
Capgemini Financial Services is a Global Strategic Business Unit that provides information technology and consultancy services to the Banking, Capital Markets and Insurance industries. Capgemini FS brings you leading insights & deep industry experience to drive the future of Financial Services. Our customers count on us for the very latest in innovative service offerings & next generation global delivery.

Let’s talk about your capability and experience:
About Capgemini
At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to becoming a carbon neutral business by 2025 and net zero by 2030.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.

For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 10 years in a row.

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion
Don’t meet every single requirement for this role? Studies have shown women and people from diverse minority backgrounds are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single requirement. At Capgemini, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply and tell us what you can bring to the role.
We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges. Description:
Req ID: 34113
Department: Joiners and Movers (39970694)
Division: N/A
Get to where you need to be. Sooner

ANZ’s award-winning graduate programs are specifically designed to fast-track the career you have been working so hard towards. You’ll be in the express lane from day one as every graduate is hand-picked and hired to fill a genuine business need. Then when you cross the finishing line, a job will be waiting for you in an area of your choice - along with a healthy “end-of-program" pay rise.

Things move fast at ANZ as we’re doing the important work that only one of Australia’s biggest banks with a global network can tackle. But don’t worry, we’re a nice bunch of people so you won’t be expected to have all the answers up front.

Instead, six monthly rotations will open your eyes to what’s possible at ANZ and what’s the best path for you to take. And the 18 or 24 months you spend on the program will be jam packed with learning and networking opportunities to set you up with the contacts, confidence, and expertise to turbo charge your career.

So don’t delay, because our plans are big - and we want you right up front with us!

About the ANZ Plus Graduate Program

As an ANZ Plus Grad, you’ll be rotating through 3 roles in different areas within ANZ Plus. This graduate program is unlike any other; imagine being at the ground level of a start-up but knowing that you have the backing of a big 4 bank behind you.

You’ll be working with the team that is behind the fastest growing digital bank in Australia that is fundamentally changing the way in which people manage their finances. With a mission of helping improve the financial well-being of everyday Australians, ANZ Plus is the best place to kickstart your career be it as software engineer, data engineer, designer or cloud specialist.

Experience a mix of skills development, regular one-on-one coffee catch ups and plenty of iterations with other graduates as well as some senior people across ANZ that you’ll love to learn from.

Work on a graduate project in the first 6 months which lets you take ownership of the ANZ Plus Hackathon! You’ll be supported by a project sponsor and a project coach but it’ll be your project to deliver, or fail to deliver... And that’s okay too, because we celebrate failures as we encourage you to fail fast and fail often because that is how you learn!

You don’t have to know everything and have all the answers, we’re all one big team looking at how we can solve some pretty tricky problems.

About You

We don’t know your name yet, but we do know that you’re curious, smart, driven and already have some great life experiences under your belt. And that is exactly what we want, along with a mix of backgrounds, opinions, and disciplines to drive the bank forward and adopt our values in all aspects of working day life.

About ANZ

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers - and that’s big.

But it’s not just our customer who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too as you continuously learn, experience new things and get the support of a community to help you take the next big steps in your career.

We are just as committed to supporting our people and giving them the opportunity to develop a career. As one of Australia’s biggest banks, and with a global network, we have many opportunities in many locations. Joining ANZ is about starting a career, not starting a job and we encourage people to look for opportunities across our bank.

Supporting the wellbeing of our people is also core at ANZ which is why we cherish the people-first culture we are famous for and why the Australian Financial Review rated us the number 1 place to work in the banking and finance industry for 2021.

Being part of ANZ means working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated, creating a great place to belong. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

Brisbane Airport - QLD, Canberra - ACT, Melbourne CBD - VIC , Perth WA
The Role
Data Scientist/Analyst

As a data scientist or analyst, you can expect every day to be different but there are a few things that you can count on having to do. In line with the expectations for each ASD level, you will be responsible for identifying suitable data sets and problems and subsequently planning and performing analysis on a wide range of data. You will do this in accordance with our legislative, policy and ethical frameworks.

Data Engineer

As a Data Engineer you will be responsible for designing, developing, and supporting ASD’s data pipelines and data processing systems to deliver mission data outcomes in accordance with our legislative, policy and ethical frameworks.



As a Data Manager you will be responsible for the management and day-to-day operations of ASD’s data systems, ensuring data quality, data integrity, and compliance with our legislative, policy and ethical frameworks.


Data professional roles within Mission Data Division (MDD) ensure that ASD analysts have access to the data and tools they require to meet ASD and ADF mission requirements. We do this through the delivery of data platforms, ensuring our data is fit for purpose, delivering bespoke mission tools and applications and providing complex analytic support, including Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence capability.

As part of your job, ASD will support you and provide opportunities to stay up-to-date with the latest trends and technologies to develop new ways to collect information and solve intelligence problems. The work we do is unique, critical and incredibly rewarding.

Description:
Why Sundrive?

SunDrive’s proprietary technology enables the use of copper instead of silver for solar cell electrodes. This technological breakthrough has significant benefits, including greater efficiency, lower cost, a scalable supply chain and more environmentally friendly production.

Founded in 2015, SunDrive is backed by some of Australia’s top venture capital firms (Blackbird, MainSequence, Virescent, Grok), tech founders and the Australian Government (CEFC, ARENA). SunDrive has quickly grown from a UNSW PhD project in a garage to producing the world’s most efficient commercial-sized solar cells.
As a Process Engineer Plating, you will work at the forefront of SunDrive’s plating process optimisation. You will be responsible for hands-on work in plating across R&D experiments as well as in production, conducting experiments and undergoing processing runs with large sample sizes to maximise the output of SunDrive’s cell technology. You will also oversee the operation and maintenance of plating equipment in the lab and on the production line. You will help develop technology and improve SunDrive's technological competitiveness. This is an important role that will have a major impact on the quality and performance of SunDrive's products.

Req ID: 30434
Department: THQ - ANZx ABT Program AU (30110519)
Division: Group Technology (T77000)
About the role

Data Engineering Manager – ANZ Plus
Location; Melbourne/Sydney
Permanent – Full Time/Part Time

At ANZx, our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We are making this happen by improving our customers’ financial wellbeing so they can achieve incredible things – be it buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small. We are looking for people who are passionate about transformational change and to help us redefine banking for the future.

Be a part of building the ideal data ecosystem from scratch. Ensuring the right data is generated from all applications, sourced at the right velocity with the complete depth and breadth to ensure complete coverage and reuse. This is your opportunity to build new, not fix old.

This is a people leadership role (up to 5 in a team) with broad responsibilities across many aspects of our data enablement value stream.

What will your day look like
Define, create and publish the data architecture standards for all applications and infrastructure across the portfolio.
Operational data solutions that will power our new mobile apps (iOS and Android)
Analytical systems that will be used to build brand new machine learning models
MarTech systems to provide personalised real-time in-context service and marketing messages to customers that are relevant, useful and sensitive
Enable and lead a team of data engineers to be the most creative and best they can be
Influence our cloud provider’s product roadmaps to ensure they meet our needs
What will you bring?

We’re trying to reimagine the way we help and interact with our customers, so we’re looking for creativity, open mind and energy

Cloud based data engineering experience, we use GCP but we’re open to your cloud experience
Proven successful implementation of large and complex data solutions using various architectural patterns such as microservices
Ability to influence both technical and business peers and stakeholders
Leadership of engineering teams, not just their technical skills, but their careers and ambitions, you’re passionate and empathetic
Lead by example – jump on the tools when required to support the team

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 30434

Capgemini FS brings you leading insights & deep industry experience to drive the future of Financial Services. Our customers count on us for the very latest in innovative service offerings & next generation global delivery.

Let’s talk about your capability and experience:
About Capgemini
At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to becoming a carbon neutral business by 2025 and net zero by 2030.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.

For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 10 years in a row.

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion
Don’t meet every single requirement for this role? Studies have shown women and people from diverse minority backgrounds are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single requirement. At Capgemini, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply and tell us what you can bring to the role.
We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges. If you are living with a disability, are gender diverse or neurodivergent and we can provide support with access requirements or by making an adjustment to our hiring process, please contact us at talentacquisitionaunz@capgemini.com

Description:
Req ID: 34113
Department: Joiners and Movers (39970694)
Division: N/A
Get to where you need to be. Sooner

ANZ’s award-winning graduate programs are specifically designed to fast-track the career you have been working so hard towards. You’ll be in the express lane from day one as every graduate is hand-picked and hired to fill a genuine business need. Then when you cross the finishing line, a job will be waiting for you in an area of your choice - along with a healthy “end-of-program" pay rise.

Things move fast at ANZ as we’re doing the important work that only one of Australia’s biggest banks with a global network can tackle. But don’t worry, we’re a nice bunch of people so you won’t be expected to have all the answers up front.

Instead, six monthly rotations will open your eyes to what’s possible at ANZ and what’s the best path for you to take. And the 18 or 24 months you spend on the program will be jam packed with learning and networking opportunities to set you up with the contacts, confidence, and expertise to turbo charge your career.

So don’t delay, because our plans are big - and we want you right up front with us!

About the ANZ Plus Graduate Program

As an ANZ Plus Grad, you’ll be rotating through 3 roles in different areas within ANZ Plus. This graduate program is unlike any other; imagine being at the ground level of a start-up but knowing that you have the backing of a big 4 bank behind you.

You’ll be working with the team that is behind the fastest growing digital bank in Australia that is fundamentally changing the way in which people manage their finances. With a mission of helping improve the financial well-being of everyday Australians, ANZ Plus is the best place to kickstart your career be it as software engineer, data engineer, designer or cloud specialist.

Experience a mix of skills development, regular one-on-one coffee catch ups and plenty of iterations with other graduates as well as some senior people across ANZ that you’ll love to learn from.

Work on a graduate project in the first 6 months which lets you take ownership of the ANZ Plus Hackathon! You’ll be supported by a project sponsor and a project coach but it’ll be your project to deliver, or fail to deliver... And that’s okay too, because we celebrate failures as we encourage you to fail fast and fail often because that is how you learn!

You don’t have to know everything and have all the answers, we’re all one big team looking at how we can solve some pretty tricky problems.

About You

We don’t know your name yet, but we do know that you’re curious, smart, driven and already have some great life experiences under your belt. And that is exactly what we want, along with a mix of backgrounds, opinions, and disciplines to drive the bank forward and adopt our values in all aspects of working day life.

About ANZ

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers - and that’s big.

But it’s not just our customer who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too as you continuously learn, experience new things and get the support of a community to help you take the next big steps in your career.

We are just as committed to supporting our people and giving them the opportunity to develop a career. As one of Australia’s biggest banks, and with a global network, we have many opportunities in many locations. Joining ANZ is about starting a career, not starting a job and we encourage people to look for opportunities across our bank.

Supporting the wellbeing of our people is also core at ANZ which is why we cherish the people-first culture we are famous for and why the Australian Financial Review rated us the number 1 place to work in the banking and finance industry for 2021.

Being part of ANZ means working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated, creating a great place to belong. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

Ready to activate your career?

Apply now for the 2024 ANZ Plus Graduate Program, click the Apply Online button below.

Saturday, 15th April 2023

For more information, visit https://au.gradconnection.com/employers/anz/

ANZ recognises the value of an inclusive and diverse work environment. We take pride in the diversity of our people and encourage applications from diverse candidates. Our recruitment decisions are based on the key inherent needs and requirements of each role and candidates are selected based on their unique strengths and characteristics.

IMPORTANT!

Please only submit one application / apply for one advertisement for the 2024 ANZ Graduate Program. You will have the opportunity to also select a second preference of stream as part of the application form.

Job Posting End Date

15th April 2023 - 11.59pm, (Melbourne Australia)

Description:
It’s official. We’re the #1 best place to work in Agriculture, Mining and Utilities awarded by @FinancialReview and @Inventium

How can you Unearth the Possibilities with Nufarm?

Based in Laverton North at our Pipe Road MHF manufacturing facility, we are looking to engage an experienced and results oriented Process Engineer to join the 2,4D Synthesis Team. This role is responsible for developing and implementing process improvement projects as well as supporting day to day operations within the Pipe Rd site.

This role will see you monitoring plant performance, ensuring we operate within defined parameters with a focus on continuously improving on safety, quality and capacity.

We’re committed to building a flexible and inclusive environment and are open to flexible working arrangements for this role.

Be part of building a better Nufarm

Oversight of operation of the manufacturing plants under the 2,4D department.

Provision of technical expertise and knowledge to assist in day-to-day troubleshooting and problem solving.

Implementation of improvement strategies including the preparation of business cases for raising of capital expenditure requests.

Analysis of plant data to develop recommendations in line with business needs.

Project scoping including development of conceptual design.

Monitoring of plant reliability and implement improvement programs in collaboration with Maintenance and Reliability teams.

Active participation in Management of Change (MOC), New Product Introduction (NPI), Unusual Incident Report (Unusual Incident Report) or IR (Injury Report).

Instigate and facilitate root cause analysis to investigate incidents of non-compliance relating to plant performance, safety, and quality with support from Formulations Process and Production Engineers.

Understand the site environmental targets and limits, promote understanding, and ensure compliance across the three plants.

Subject Matter Expert on “Lean Tools” (5S, TPM, RCA, etc.)

Subject Matter Expert on "Lean Tools" (5S, Total Productive Maintenance (TPM), Root Cause Analysis (RCA), etc.) for area

What do you bring?

This role would suit a degree qualified Chemical Engineer with demonstrated extensive experience in a Process Engineering role, ideally in a chemical or FMCG manufacturing environment. The ideal candidate will have excellent investigative and analytical skills with the ability to build and maintain effective stakeholder relationships. Demonstrated technical expertise and the ability to implement change are pivotal for success in the role. Most importantly you are looking for a role within a global organisation that supports and develops its employees!

If you want to be a part of a thriving, supportive environment and are inspired by the prospect of being a part of something bigger, we’d love to hear from you. Nufarm is proud to be recognised as an endorsed employer of choice for all woman by Work180.

About the role

Modern frameworks & languages. Brand new applications. At a bank – really? This isn’t just any normal software engineering team; this is a team where you’ll be building reusable services that help us create amazing experiences for our customers - it’s a pretty big deal! Our platforms process over 1.3 billion transactions daily, and we need some curious minds to help us solve the problems we encounter in delivering better banking to customers.

We’re also on a transformational journey – we’ve been around a while, and we need people like you to join us to create new experiences that our customers will love. By reshaping how we work, we’re enabling our people to deliver the types of experiences our customers will rave about to their family, friends and Instagram followers. We want to shape a world where people and communities thrive, and that starts by having fabulous and talented people working towards a shared mission who are determined to drive positive change.

Here’s how YOU can make an impact...

You’ll be coding away at your mac, developing software that will be used by over 2 million customers every day.

Bring your deep experience with prominent languages and frameworks such as Go, Python, C#, Java, React to name a few.

Ability to tackle and deal with the complexities of some real-world issues.

A confident understanding in engineering principles, data structures and algorithms.

We want to shape a world where people and communities thrive, and that only starts by having really awesome and talented people coming into work each and every day who are determined to drive positive change.

So, why join us?

At ANZ, everything we do boils down to ‘why’ – our purpose – to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We're just as focused on seeing our people thrive as well as our customers. We'll give you every opportunity to develop your career. We are responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter the most, energising our people, eliminating waste and reducing bureaucracy.

A happy workplace is a thriving one. So in order to attract and keep the best talent, and say thanks for the hard work, we make sure all our employees are rewarded.

We work flexibly at ANZ and encourage you to talk to us about how this role can be flexible for you and any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

Description:
Responsibilities
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.

Why Join Us
At TikTok, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for more than 1 billion users on our platform. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok.

About the TikTok Engineering Team
We are building up an engineering team for core TikTok product in Australia, to ensure TikTok continues a healthy growth, deliver the best product experience to all of our users, build the most attractive features to help users on enjoying their time on TikTok, earn trust on privacy protection, and more.

We are looking for talented individuals to join us in 2023. As a graduate, you will get unparalleled opportunities for you to kickstart your career, pursue bold ideas and explore limitless growth opportunities. Co-create a future driven by your inspiration with TikTok.

Candidates can apply to a maximum of two positions and will be considered for jobs in the order you apply. The application limit is applicable to TikTok and its affiliates' jobs globally. Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis - we encourage you to apply early.

Responsibilities
Qualifications
TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

In the spirit of reconciliation, TikTok acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their Elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.

By submitting an application for this role, you accept and agree to our global applicant privacy policy, which may be accessed here: https://careers.tiktok.com/legal/privacy.

If you have any questions, please reach out to us at apac-earlycareers@tiktok.com.

Job_title: Expressions of Interest - Data Engineer, Data & Analytics
Description:
At EY, you’ll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. And we’re counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all.

What if your most rewarding experiences couldn’t be captured by a resume?

At EY we believe that whoever you are, your uniqueness helps us stand apart.

We bring together extraordinary people, like you, to build a better working world. This role is open to applicants across Adelaide, Melbourne, Perth, Brisbane, Canberra and Sydney.

Help us make a big green dent in the universe. We're on a mission to drive the global renewable energy revolution, and we need loads more people to help us make our vision a reality.

About Octopus Energy

Since 2015, Octopus has been on a mission to bring affordable, green energy to the world. With the help of our in-house developed technology platform, Kraken, we’ve become the 4th largest energy supplier in the UK, opened retailers in 5 other countries, and licensed our software to retail giants including E.ON in the UK and Origin Energy in Australia. We’ve reinvented energy products with smart, data-driven tariffs to balance customer demand with renewable generation - and we’re the biggest investor in renewable generation in the UK.

We've since expanded our tentacles to Australia, and we are now looking for Data Engineer, based in Melbourne, Wellington or remote in either New Zealand or Australia. Working with Octopus Energy is a chance to join an exciting scale-up business within the energy supply sector, one that’s at the forefront of changing the landscape of the energy industry across the world. A role with us offers you the chance to contribute to building world-class operations that will catapult you into a fantastic career.

Description:
Come and join a thriving company and become part of a diverse global collective of free-thinkers, entrepreneurs and industry experts who are all driven to use technology to reimagine what’s possible. Capgemini. Get the future you want.

For more about why Capgemini https://www.capgemini.com/au-en/careers/why-join-capgemini/

Let’s talk about the role and responsibilities:
Collaborate with business analysts and end-users to identify requirements and develop technical specifications for software applications

Let's talk about the team:

Capgemini Financial Services is a Global Strategic Business Unit that provides information technology and consultancy services to the Banking, Capital Markets and Insurance industries. Capgemini FS brings you leading insights & deep industry experience to drive the future of Financial Services. Our customers count on us for the very latest in innovative service offerings & next generation global delivery.


Let’s talk about your capability and experience:

About Capgemini

At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to becoming a carbon neutral business by 2025 and net zero by 2030.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.

For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 10 years in a row.

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion

Don’t meet every single requirement for this role? Studies have shown women and people from diverse minority backgrounds are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single requirement. At Capgemini, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply and tell us what you can bring to the role.
We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges. If you are living with a disability, are gender diverse or neurodivergent and we can provide support with access requirements or by making an adjustment to our hiring process, please contact us at talentacquisitionaunz@capgemini.com

Description:
Req ID: 30433
Department: THQ - ANZx ABT Program AU (30110519)
Division: Group Technology (T77000)
About the role
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head
Use Google’s cloud services to deliver real-time insights about customer behaviour
Be part of something different - working in an agile way to innovate and deliver quality outcomes at pace

At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We’re making this happen by improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our customers so they can achieve incredible things– whether they’re buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small. Join us as we reimagine our customer propositions and services using the latest platforms and technology, to better support our customers’ financial wellbeing

The Data Engineering position is critical to making this happen and your key accountabilities will include:

Building real-time analytical capability to power
Experiences within the mobile app
Informing marketing and servicing messaging
Enriching our data lake
Build data quality automated frameworks across a multi-cloud data and on premises environments
Building highly optimised data models with multiple interface types for data consumers
What will your day look like
Working in an agile framework with a team of Data Engineers to deliver data solutions for our transformation including:
Building optimized data solutions and ingestion patterns with considerations for security and data governance
Building data pipelines and a real-time data eco-system to provide interactive customer experiences that will feed data into other systems via multiple interface types.
Define and publish the data architecture standards for all applications and infrastructure across the portfolio
Foster collaboration across teams, functions, regions and divisions using a range of influencing and negotiation strategies to establish mutually beneficial partnerships with key stakeholders
What will you bring?

To grow and be successful in this role, you will ideally bring the following:

Cloud based data engineering experience
Proven successful building large data solutions
Ability to work collaboratively with technical and business teams
Ability to multi-task, highly adaptable to change and ambiguity
Proactive, shows initiative and keen to try new things i.e. new technologies

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. We encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

To find out more about working at ANZ or to view other opportunities visit www.careers.anz.com. You may apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 30433

Description:
Company Description

It all started with an idea at Block in 2013. Initially built to take the pain out of peer-to-peer payments, Cash App has gone from a simple product with a single purpose to a dynamic ecosystem, developing unique financial products, including Afterpay, to provide a better way to send, spend, invest, borrow and save to our 47 million monthly active customers. We want to redefine the world’s relationship with money to make it more relatable, instantly available, and universally accessible. This is our mission, and it’s why working at Cash App means so much more than a job.

Today, Cash App has thousands of employees working globally across office and remote locations, with a culture geared toward innovation, collaboration and impact. We’ve been a distributed team since day one, and many of our roles can be done remotely from the countries where Cash App operates. No matter the location, we tailor our experience to ensure our employees are creative, productive, and happy.

Check out our locations, benefits, and more at cash.app/careers!

Description:
Req ID: 30433
Department: THQ - ANZx ABT Program AU (30110519)
Division: Group Technology (T77000)
About the role
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head
Use Google’s cloud services to deliver real-time insights about customer behaviour
Be part of something different - working in an agile way to innovate and deliver quality outcomes at pace

At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We’re making this happen by improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our customers so they can achieve incredible things– whether they’re buying a home, building a business or saving for things big or small. Join us as we reimagine our customer propositions and services using the latest platforms and technology, to better support our customers’ financial wellbeing

The Data Engineering position is critical to making this happen and your key accountabilities will include:

Building real-time analytical capability to power
Experiences within the mobile app
Informing marketing and servicing messaging
Enriching our data lake
Build data quality automated frameworks across a multi-cloud data and on premises environments
Building highly optimised data models with multiple interface types for data consumers
What will your day look like
Working in an agile framework with a team of Data Engineers to deliver data solutions for our transformation including:
Building optimized data solutions and ingestion patterns with considerations for security and data governance
Building data pipelines and a real-time data eco-system to provide interactive customer experiences that will feed data into other systems via multiple interface types.
Define and publish the data architecture standards for all applications and infrastructure across the portfolio
Foster collaboration across teams, functions, regions and divisions using a range of influencing and negotiation strategies to establish mutually beneficial partnerships with key stakeholders
What will you bring?

To grow and be successful in this role, you will ideally bring the following:

Cloud based data engineering experience
Proven successful building large data solutions
Ability to work collaboratively with technical and business teams
Ability to multi-task, highly adaptable to change and ambiguity
Proactive, shows initiative and keen to try new things i.e. new technologies

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So, why join us?

There’s something special about being part of ANZ. From the moment you join us, you’re part of a team working towards a common goal: improving the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

But it’s not just our customers who’ll feel your impact. You’ll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you’ll have the resources and community you need to take the next big step in your career, towards even bigger things in the future.

We offer a range of benefits tailored to the countries in which we operate including Health and Wellbeing programs and flexible working arrangements.

You’ll also enjoy working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. Description:
Come and join a thriving company and become part of a diverse global collective of free-thinkers, entrepreneurs and industry experts who are all driven to use technology to reimagine what’s possible. Capgemini. Get the future you want.

For more about why Capgemini https://www.capgemini.com/au-en/careers/why-join-capgemini/

This role could be in Sydney, Melbourne, Canberra, Brisbane, or Adelaide.



Let’s talk about the role and responsibilities:
Collaborate with business analysts and end-users to identify requirements and develop technical specifications for software applications

Let's talk about the team:

Capgemini Financial Services is a Global Strategic Business Unit that provides information technology and consultancy services to the Banking, Capital Markets and Insurance industries. Capgemini FS brings you leading insights & deep industry experience to drive the future of Financial Services. Our customers count on us for the very latest in innovative service offerings & next generation global delivery.


Let’s talk about your capability and experience:

About Capgemini

At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to becoming a carbon neutral business by 2025 and net zero by 2030.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.

For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 10 years in a row.

Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion

Don’t meet every single requirement for this role? Studies have shown women and people from diverse minority backgrounds are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single requirement. At Capgemini, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply and tell us what you can bring to the role.
We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges.
